<title type="html"><![CDATA[10/10(Thu) Why the way we talk to children really matters / Why do people join cults]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=323&amp;p=339#p339"><![CDATA[
<span style="font-weight: bold">Session One: Why the way we talk to children really matters ?</span><br /><br />Please click the following link to read the article.<br /><a href="http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20191001-the-word-gap-that-affects-how-your-babys-brain-grows" class="postlink">http://www.bbc.com/future/story/20191001-the-word-gap-that-affects-how-your-babys-brain-grows</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />Q1. Do you agree that the quality of the conversation to children is important?<br />Q2. Is there a word gap in children between lower-income and higher-income families? <br />Q3. Can you share experience in conversation when talking to a newborn?<br />Q4. How do you communicate effectively with kids?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Session Two: Why do people join cults ?</span><br /><br />Please click the following link to watch the video.<br /><a href="https://www.ted.com/talks/janja_lalich_why_do_people_join_cults#t-367292" class="postlink">https://www.ted.com/talks/janja_lalich_why_do_people_join_cults#t-367292</a><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Discussion:</span><br />Q1. What is your opinion on religious cults? What do you consider a cult?<br />Q2. Why do higher education people join cults?<br />Q3. Why do people follow dictators?<br />Q4. What would you do if you found out a coworker who you like is a current member of an abusive religious cult?<br /><br />***************************************************************************************<br />Suggested Agenda<br />7:00 p.m. --7:30 p.m. Free talk<br />7:30 p.m. --8:10 p.m. First topic discussion<br />8:10 p.m. --8:40 p.m. Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:40 p.m.-- 9.:15 p.m. Second topic discussion<br />9:15 p.m.-- 9:30 p.m. Presentation (Participants that haven't presented yet are invited)<br /><br />speaker time: 2 minutes for each speaker<br />host time: 3 minutes<br /><br />The meeting place of Thursday:<br />丹堤咖啡寶慶店：台北市延平南路107號2F (上樓右邊第三區塊)<br />捷運資訊： 近台北捷運–西門站 (4號出口步行約2分鐘，康是美隔壁)<br />丹堤低消: NT$80元<br />最自由的全英文會話聚會,前三次不用交會費,加入會員終生會費NT$500，帶著開放與熱情來學英文<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=49">josh</a> — Sun Oct 06, 2019 10:39 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
